1 Sec. 3. 24 App. V.S.A. chapter 129C is added to read:
2 CHAPTER 129C. TOWN OF MORRISTOWN
3 § 1. CORPORATE EXISTENCE RETAINED
4 The inhabitants of the Town of Morristown, within the corporate limits now
5 established, shall continue to be a municipal corporation by the name of the
6 Town of Morristown.
7 § 2. GENERAL LAW; APPLICATION
8 Except when changed or modified by this charter, or by any lawful
9 regulation or ordinance of the Town, all of the statutes of the State relating to
10 municipalities shall apply to the Town.
11 § 3. TOWN MANAGER
12 (a) The Town Manager shall be the chief executive officer and the head of
13 the administrative branch of the Town government and shall be responsible to
14 the Selectboard for the efficient administration of the municipal affairs of the
15 Town.
16 (b) The Town Manager shall have the authority to hire, appoint, discipline,
17 and remove all Town employees, subject to the provisions of personnel rules
18 approved by the Selectboard. The Town Manager may authorize a department
19 head to hire, appoint, discipline, or remove an employee, subject to the
20 Manager’s discretion and supervision.
